7 Restoring backups
*******************

When rsnapshot is first run, it will create the snapshot_root directory
(`/.snapshots/' by default). It assigns this directory the permissions
700, and for good reason. The snapshot root will probably contain files
owned by all sorts of users on your system. If any of these files are
writeable (and of course some of them will be), the users will still
have write access to their files. Thus, if they can see the snapshots
directly, they can modify them, and the integrity of the snapshots can
not be guaranteed.

   For example, if a user had write permission to the backups and
accidentally ran `rm -rf /', they would delete all their files in their
home directory and all the files they owned in the backups!

