7.1 root only
=============

The simplest, but least flexible solution, is to simply deny non-root
users access to the snapshot root altogether. The root user will still
have access of course, and as with all other aspects of system
administration, must be trusted not to go messing with things too much.
However, by simply denying access to everyone, the root user will be
the only one who can pull backups. This may or may not be desirable,
depending on your situation. For a small setup or a single-user
machine, this may be all you need.


